# Edge-Net Dashboard – environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env.local` and customize. All values are optional; defaults are
# tuned to ship the minimum viable dashboard (no unfinished surfaces visible).
#
# Variables MUST be prefixed with `VITE_` to be exposed to the client by Vite.
# See: https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Feature flags for surfaces that are not yet production-ready.
#
# Defaults are `false`. Set to the literal string `true` to opt in.
# Anything else (empty, "1", "yes", etc.) resolves to `false`.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# PiKey "Restore from encrypted backup" flow inside the Identity panel.
# Requires `PiKey.restoreFromBackup` in the EdgeNet WASM module — see
# src/stores/identityStore.ts. The password import path throws today; this
# flag lets opt-in builds reach the throw without changing default behavior.
VITE_ENABLE_PIKEY_RESTORE=false
